), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Pytfolde was born about 1478, in England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Joan."},"et":{"About 1478–":"umbes 1478–Surnud","1486–Female":"1486–Surnud","1501–Male":"1501–Surnud","1478–Male":"1478–Surnud","1501":"1501","1478":"1478","1486":"1486","About 1478":"umbes 1478","Allington, Dorsetshire, England, United Kingdom":"Allington, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"About 1478–":"noin 1478–Kuollut","1486–Female":"1486–Kuollut","1501–Male":"1501–Kuollut","1478–Male":"1478–Kuollut","1501":"1501","1478":"1478","1486":"1486","About 1478":"noin 1478","Allington, Dorsetshire, England, United Kingdom":"Allington, Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"About 1478–":"environ 1478–Décédé","1486–Female":"1486–Décédée","1501–Male":"1501–Décédé","1478–Male":"1478–Décédé","1501":"1501","1478":"1478","1486":"1486","About 1478":"environ 1478","Allington, Dorsetshire, England, United Kingdom":"Allington, Dorset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert Pytfolde est né environ 1478, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Joan."},"de":{"About 1478–":"um 1478–Verstorben","1486–Female":"1486–Verstorben","1501–Male":"1501–Verstorben","1478–Male":"1478–Verstorben","1501":"1501","1478":"1478","1486":"1486","About 1478":"um 1478","Allington, Dorsetshire, Englan